\frac{n^2}{n!}=\frac{a_0+a_1n+a_2n(n-1)}{n!}=\frac{a_0}{n!}+\frac{a_1}{(n-1)!}+\frac{a_2}{(n-2)!}
\implies n^2=a_0+n(a_1-a_2)+a_2n^2
\implies a_2=1,a_1-a_2=0\iff a_1=a_2,a_0=0
